{"id":"321337672_Introduction_to_Property_Testing","abstract":"Property testing is concerned with the design of super-fast algorithms for the structural analysis of large quantities of data. The aim is to unveil global features of the data, such as determining whether the data has a particular property or estimating global parameters. Remarkably, it is possible for decisions to be made by accessing only a small portion of the data. Property testing focuses on properties and parameters that go beyond simple statistics. This book provides an extensive and authoritative introduction to property testing. It provides a wide range of algorithmic techniques for the design and analysis of tests for algebraic properties, properties of Boolean functions, graph properties, and properties of distributions.","authors":["Oded Goldreich"],"meta":["November 2017","DOI:10.1017/9781108135252"],"references":["311736761_A_Characterization_of_Constant-Sample_Testable_Properties","309797564_A_Unified_Maximum_Likelihood_Approach_for_Optimal_Distribution_Property_Estimation","303798327_Non-interactive_proofs_of_proximity","280330247_Optimal_Testing_for_Properties_of_Distributions","260251427_Best_of_Two_Local_Models_Local_Centralized_and_Local_Distributed_Algorithms","225128551_Improved_Testing_Algorithms_for_Monotonicity","225118379_Property_Testing_of_Massively_Parametrized_Problems_-_A_Survey","221498619_Testing_Properties_of_Sparse_Images","220974793_Transitive-Closure_Spanners_A_Survey","220974790_Short_Locally_Testable_Codes_and_Proofs_A_Survey_in_Two_Parts","220618026_On_Proximity-Oblivious_Testing","220616808_Algorithmic_Aspects_of_Property_Testing_in_the_Dense_Graphs_Model","220431215_Proofs_that_Yield_Nothing_But_Their_Validity_for_All_Languages_in_NP_Have_Zero-Knowledge_Proof_Systems","220138612_On_Proximity-Oblivious_Testing","220138415_A_Note_on_Adaptivity_in_Testing_Properties_of_Bounded_Degree_Graphs","220137867_Introduction_to_Testing_Graph_Properties","340425979_On_the_Rel